value.0: Traveller?
Hahaha, her child? Hahaha! That's Lakhesi for you.
Monty is Lakhesi's dog. Saw it head towards the temple grounds. Probably ended up being zombie food.
Watch out, traveller, the temple grounds are not safe.

Monty is Lakhesi's dog. Saw it head towards the temple grounds. Probably ended up being zombie food.
You're either suicidal or stupid. Or both. But if you're so eager to venture forth, perhaps you can find out what happened to Yiolin.
A scout that disappeared this morning. Apparently, some heard her talk about a secret passage that could take us past the undead in the courtyard and into the inner cloister.
We were sent here to find the source of the corruption that took over the temple.

The Evergreen Temple is a sacred place for our people. Our High Priestess and the warrior priests have kept Mort'ul's minions at bay for years. At least, until a few months ago when a sudden darkness befell upon the whole temple, wrapping the inner cloister in an unpenetrable barrier.

However, everything appeared to have stayed quiet for all this time, for when we arrived three days ago, there hadn't been any signs of getting in or getting out. But then two nights ago, it happened...

The barrier suddenly bursted and out of it came... our... [The Captain takes a small pause to recompose himself] our own priests, twisted, empty eyed, chanting in unison and attacking everything in their path.
We were vastly outnumbered. We got pushed further and further back until we ended out of the courtyard. And then, they stopped advancing. We were injured, tired, demoralized, so we set up camp.
We're waiting.
For reinforcements. Until they arrive we must keep to our mission.
